1 sess ions during a semester, or a student’s behavior during tutoring
2 sessions requires disciplinary action, the student may be removed
3 from the cohort. The performance of a student subject to the
4 provisions of this paragraph shall not count against the high dosage
5 tutor.
6 I. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules to
7 implement the provisions of this section.
8 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-180.1 of Title 70, unless
10 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
12 for the State Department of Education to be designated the “High
13 Dosage Tutoring Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing
14 fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of
15 all monies received by the State Department of Education from gifts,
16 grants, donations, bequests, federal funds provided for the purpose
17 of funding high dosage tutoring, or state appropriations provided
18 for the purpose of implementing the provisions of Section 1 of this
19 act. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
20 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the State
21 Department of Education for the purpose provided for in this
22 section. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants
23 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
24
